            . (Police-constable N 115.) I saw the prisoner with this wheel; I asked him how he came to take it - he said through being out 
of employ, and he had no money nor victuals - that he was glad he was stopped, as he wished to be sent out of the country.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I did it from distress.</p>
